The '''2009 AFF U-16 Youth Championship''' was due to take place in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] between the 20 July and 2 August 2009, it was later moved to start on 6 August until 19 August<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aseanfootball.org/news_d.asp?id=883|title=Schedule change for AFF under-16|publisher=ASEAN Football Federation|date=27 May 2009|accessdate=31 July 2009}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> but was eventually canceled one month prior to the opening day due to the [[Influenza A virus subtype H1N1|H1N1 virus]] in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aseanfootball.org/news_d.asp?id=931|title=AFF U16 meet in Bangkok postponed|publisher=ASEAN Football Federation|date=9 July 2009|accessdate=12 August 2009}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

