==Nepal== Some of the highest elevations on the planet lie in Nepal. Eight out of fourteen highest peaks in the world lie in the Nepalese Himalaya including the highest peak of the World, Mt. Everest (8848 m).<ref>Nations online. [http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/nepal.htm] Retrieved on October 20, 2011.</ref> During a tropical depression that affected the Indian Subcontinent in 2004, {{convert|51.3|mm|in}} of rain fell at Kathmandu airport in the 24‑hour period ending at 1200 UTC on October 7.<ref name="PADGETTOCT2004"/>
