{{other uses|Maiden Voyage (disambiguation)}}
{{citation style|date=December 2016}}
The '''maiden voyage''' of a [[ship]], [[aircraft]] or other craft is the first journey made by the craft in its intended duty. A number of [[tradition]]s and [[superstition]]s are associated with it{{Vague|date=December 2016}}.

==Ships lost during maiden voyage==
===Naval ships===
* [[Vasa (ship)|''Vasa'']] (1628)
* [[SS Georgiana|''Georgiana'']] (1863)
* [[Flach (submarine)|''Flach'']] (1866)
* {{MV|Posidonia|1939|2}} (1940){{I sup|1}}
* [[German battleship Bismarck|''Bismarck'']] (1941){{I sup|1}}
* {{ship|RFA|Dinsdale|X106|2}} (1942){{I sup|1}}
* [[Japanese aircraft carrier Shinano|''Shinano'']] (1944){{I sup|1}}

