'''Semyon Alekseyevich Fedorets''' (Semen A. Fedorets) was a [[MiG-15]] pilot of the [[Soviet Union]]. He was a [[flying ace]] during the [[Korean war]], with 7 victories.<ref name="KT6">{{harvnb|Krylov|Tepsurkaev|2008|p=6}}</ref> ==Career== In 1941, Semyon Fedorets graduated from Dnepropetrovsk Aeroclub and entered the Military Aviation School in [[Odessa]]. After graduation, he was sent to the [[Leningrad Front]] in the [[403rd Fighter Aviation Regiment]]. Young pilots to combat operations were allowed only by May 1944, when the front moved away from [[Leningrad]]. Thus, He did not actually participate in the battles of the [[Great Patriotic War]].
After the war, in September 1949, was transferred to the airfield Voskresensk (Far East), where he was appointed commander. In April 1952, his unit was sent to [[China]], to the airfield of [[Anshan]] City. December 17, 1953, shot down his first [[F-86]] Sabre. On February 19, 1953, he was appointed squadron commander of the [[913th Fighter Regiment]] of the [[32nd Fighter Aviation Division]].
Flying a [[MiG-15]], during the [[Korean War|fighting in Korea]], he shot down 7 enemy aircraft, in 98 combat sorties and 40 air engagement.<ref>{{cite book| author = М. Ю. Быков | chapter = | chapter-url = | format = | url = | title = Все Асы Сталина 1936—1953 гг. | orig-year = | agency = | edition = Научно-популярное издание {{nowrap|1500 экз}} |location= М. |year= 2014 |publisher= ООО «Яуза-пресс» |at= |volume= |issue = | pages = 1226| page = | series = Элитная энциклопедия ВВС | isbn = 978-5-9955-0712-3| ref = }}</ref> == See also == *[[List of Korean War flying aces]]
